New Features and Important Changes in GammaLib 00-04-06

Author(s) : Juergen Knoedlseder

February 21, 2011


1. Introduction
---------------
This document briefly summarizes module by module the most important changes
made since the last release of GammaLib.


2. Configuration
-----------------
Add back autogen.sh script is release for developers


3. Application module
---------------------
Replace par() method by operator[]


4. FITS I/O Interface
---------------------
None


5. Linear algebra module
------------------------
Use operator[] instead of operator() for vector element access in GVector
class.


6. Model module
---------------
Introduce GModelExtendedSource for extended gamma-ray sources. Their spatial
component is implemented by the new class GModelRadial which defines
axisymmetric spatial models. The following radial models have been
implemented
- GModelRadialDisk  - a disk of uniform intensity
- GModelRadialGauss - a 2D Gaussian shaped intensity distribution
- GModelRadialShell - a SNR shell toy model
Radial models have their own registry class GModelRadialRegistry.

Use now operator[] for model parameter access instead of par() method.

Add GModelPar::hasgrad() method to signal parameters with analytical
gradients.


7. Numerics module
------------------
Add new gradient methods in GDerivative. In particular, a simple difference
method is now used to compite fast and robust numerical gradients.


8. Observation module
---------------------
Compute numerical gradients for free parameters without analytical gradients.

Implement extended source support in GResponse base class (binned and unbinned
analyses).

Use now operator[] for observation access.


9. Optimization module
----------------------
None


10. Sky module
--------------
Add GSkyDir posang() method for computation of position angles.


11. Support module
------------------
None


12. XML module
--------------
None


13. Multi-wavelength interface
------------------------------
None


14. Fermi-LAT interface
----------------------
None


15. CTA interface
-----------------
Implement extended source support in response class.

